The products, which were distributed nationwide and to foreign countries including Russia and South Korea by Thorn Apple Valley's Forrest City plant, may be contaminated with Listeria monocytogenes, according to the U.S. Agriculture Department's Food Safety and Inspection Service announced.
Pregnant women, the newborn, older adults and people with weakened immune systems are especially at risk.
Based on the findings and conditions at the plant, the agency concluded there may be a public health risk associated with the product.
About 1,800 cases of food poisoning caused by listeria are reported in the United States each year.
